                <h3>Stay Hydrated</h3>
                <p>Drinking enough water daily is crucial for regulating body temperature, keeping joints lubricated, and improving sleep quality and mood.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3>Incorporate Strength Training</h3>
                <p>Aim for at least two non-consecutive days per week of strength training to increase bone density and build a stronger metabolism.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3>Prioritize Sleep</h3>
                <p>Aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep per night. It helps in muscle recovery, regulates hormones, and improves cognitive function.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3>Mindful Eating</h3>
                <p>Pay attention to your food and how it makes you feel. Eating mindfully can help prevent overeating and improve digestion.</p>
            </div>
             <div class="tip-card">
                <h3>Warm-Up and Cool-Down</h3>
                <p>Always start your workout with a 5-10 minute warm-up and end with a cool-down to prevent injury and improve recovery.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3>Listen to Your Body</h3>
                <p>Rest days are as important as workout days. Pay attention to signs of fatigue or pain to avoid overtraining.</p>
            </div>
